SUMMARY:Katie Shesko
LOCATION:Hero Stage/Europa
DESCRIPTION:Flute Enchantress Katie Shesko is weaving melodies from video 
 games and anime realms. In her home studio\, she crafts and records captiv
 ating video game soundscapes that enchant gamers and anime enthusiasts ali
 ke. Join her on a symphonic journey through animated worlds. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:daaf898c464467497b0290cb005d40f6
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T150000
DTEND:20250411T155500
SUMMARY:Composing with Global Music Traditions for Video Games
LOCATION:Panels 2/Conference Room D
DESCRIPTION:Video games allow players to explore virtual worlds\, sometime
 s fantastical and other times reminiscent of our own\, real world. The vis
 uals and audio of these virtual worlds establish a sense of place and time
 \, based on the players’ conceptions of cultural and historical signifie
 rs. Intended for composers and music nerds\, this panel led by composer Jo
 hn MacDonald will explore difficulties encountered when composing video ga
 me music that draws from real-world musical traditions\, including preserv
 ation (or lack thereof) of musical traditions\, problematic musical misrep
 resentation\, research methods of non-Western music for Western-trained mu
 sicians\, and defying or reinforcing culture-specific tropes. 
END:VEVENT
