SUMMARY:Video Game Music Education for Everyone
LOCATION:Panels 1/Conference Room E
DESCRIPTION:Let's talk about teaching video game music education! Dr. Nico
 le Harvey (@RedAuxPDX) Associate Professor at the University of Portland\,
  will discuss her approach in teaching game music history and appreciation
  to a mostly STEM-focused student base\, as well as the development of her
  video game music class into the university's core humanities curriculum. 
 Jeremy Tellock (@DucksinDisguise)\, Director of Production and Design at P
 ixel Pond will discuss teaching students to compose music for games utiliz
 ing DAWs and FL Studio. 
END:VEVENT
