SUMMARY:Transcribing VGM
LOCATION:Panels 2/Conference Room D
DESCRIPTION:This presentation will demonstrate the transcription process f
 or video game music\, specifically games from the third-fifth generations\
 , where the music was "performed" by the game's sound chip. Having these s
 cores is helpful for study and arrangement purposes\, but the process in c
 reating them helps one understand the technology of these consoles and how
  the composer had to work with this tech in order to create the sounds the
 y wanted. 
END:VEVENT
